Признаки¶

( ):

  • "timestamp" - timestamp field for grouping the data
  • "cnt" - the count of a new bike shares - target variable
  • "t1" - real temperature in C
  • "t2" - temperature in C "feels like"
  • "hum" - humidity in percentage
  • "wind_speed" - wind speed in km/h
  • "weather_code" - category of the weather
  • "is_holiday" - boolean field - 1 holiday / 0 non holiday
  • "is_weekend" - boolean field - 1 if the day is weekend
  • "season" - category field meteorological seasons: 0-spring ; 1-summer; 2-fall; 3-winter.

"weathe_code" category description:

  • 1 = Clear ; mostly clear but have some values with haze/fog/patches of fog/ fog in vicinity
  • 2 = scattered clouds / few clouds
  • 3 = Broken clouds
  • 4 = Cloudy
  • 7 = Rain/ light Rain shower/ Light rain
  • 10 = rain with thunderstorm
  • 26 = snowfall
  • 94 = Freezing Fog

In [81]:
for i in range(0,len(data['timestamp'])):

 
    
    hour=datetime.datetime.strptime(data['timestamp'][i],"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S").hour
    
    if hour>=0 and hour<=6:
        data['timestamp'][i]='night'
    elif hour>=6 and hour<=12:
        data['timestamp'][i]='morning'
    elif hour>=12 and hour<=17:
        data['timestamp'][i]='day'
    elif hour>=17 and hour<=23:
        data['timestamp'][i]='evening'

                                 y_true=val_y)

mae = metrics.mean_absolute_error(y_pred=y_pred_lasso, 
                                 y_true=val_y)
def mape_func(y_true, y_pred): 
  #  y_true, y_pred = np.array(y_true), np.array(y_pred)
    return np.mean(np.abs((y_true - y_pred) / y_true)) * 100

mape=mape_func(val_y,y_pred_lasso)

R2 = metrics.r2_score(y_pred=y_pred_lasso, 
                                 y_true=val_y)
